tate channel inputs are not superior in the\nasymptotic limit to non-adaptive product state strategies. (4) As an\napplication of our findings, we address the discrimination power of quantum\nchannels and show that adaptive strategies with classical feedback and no\nquantum memory at the input do not increase the discrimination power of\nentanglement-breaking channel beyond non-adaptive tensor product input\nstrategies.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 12 Nov 2020 18:40:47 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 14 Jun 2021 14:37:32 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-06-15"}
