ison with the\nliterature, we find no clear evidence that the cutoffs in obscured and\nunobscured AGN are substantially different. Our analysis highlights the\nimportance of carefully considering partial and potentially degenerate\nconstraints on the coronal high-energy cutoff in AGN.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 12 Nov 2020 18:57:04 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-12-16"}
