ctive\ndeuterium fractionation chemistry in multiple disk regions around TW Hya, but\nnot in the cold planetesimal-forming midplane and in the inner disk. More\nobservations are needed to explore whether deuterium fractionation is actually\nabsent in these latter regions, and if its absence is a common feature, or\nsomething peculiar to the old TW Hya disk.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 13 Nov 2020 06:12:22 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-01-06"}
