trons in\nstates where major ejections are observed. We find a dependence of the photon\nindex of the power law as a function of the strong orbital modulation of the\nsource in the Flaring InterMediate (FIM) state. This dependence could be due to\na higher absorption when Cygnus X-3 is behind its companion. However, the\nuncertainties on the density column prevent us from drawing conclusions.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 13 Nov 2020 11:19:16 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-01-20"}
